      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you suspect nitrogen deficiency, you can add a balanced fertilizer specifically formulated for tomatoes, following the instructions on the label for application rate and timing. Make sure to choose a fertilizer with an N-P-K ratio suitable for your soil's pH. To prevent nutrient loss to pests, use a physical barrier like row covers or fine mesh to protect your plants, and consider introducing beneficial insects like ladybugs or lacewings that prey on common tomato pests.",
